============================================================
Direct Rust dependencies (dbmd-cli — the thin `dbmd` binary)
============================================================

`dbmd-cli` parses args + formats output. Beyond the shared library deps
(serde / serde_json) it adds the argument parser, plus the embedded-
ripgrep trio that `dbmd search`'s free-text step runs in-handler over the
candidate set `dbmd-core` resolves (plan Block 4). The ripgrep crates are
the same ones `dbmd-core` already depends on (re-listed here because they
are now also direct dependencies of the binary crate):

- clap             4.x      MIT OR Apache-2.0   — derive-based subcommand
                                                  parser, --help, exit codes
  (transitive: clap_builder, clap_derive, clap_lex, anstream, anstyle,
   anstyle-parse, anstyle-query, colorchoice, is_terminal_polyfill,
   utf8parse, strsim — all MIT OR Apache-2.0)
- grep             0.3.x    MIT OR Unlicense    — embedded ripgrep search engine
                                                  (`dbmd search` free-text scan)
- ignore           0.4.x    MIT OR Unlicense    — embedded ripgrep dir walk
                                                  (no-filter candidate set)
- regex            1.x      MIT OR Apache-2.0   — query-regex validation +
                                                  link-target normalization
- chrono           0.4.x    MIT OR Apache-2.0   — RFC3339/date parsing for
                                                  `dbmd log` (entry timestamp,
                                                  `since`) + `index query` windows
- serde_norway     0.9.x    MIT OR Apache-2.0   — render a frontmatter YAML
                                                  scalar for `dbmd fm get`

